dcterms:description: A real-world dataset collected from a college, containing digital footprints of student behaviors for multiple prediction tasks.

Predicting the Number of Failed Courses

dcterms:description: Records of students entering the library, used to analyze student behaviors and predict academic performance.
dcterms:title: Library Entrance Records

dcterms:description: Records of students entering the dormitory, used to analyze student behaviors and predict academic performance.
dcterms:title: Dormitory Entrance Records

dcterms:description: Demographic information of students, including attributes such as place of birth, nationality, gender, grade, school, and department.
dcterms:title: Demographic Records

dcterms:description: Records of final course grades for students, used to predict academic performance.
dcterms:title: Student Final Course Grade Records

dcterms:description: Historical records of Weighted Average Grades (WAG) for students, used to analyze academic performance trends.
dcterms:title: Historical WAG (Weighted Average Grade) sequence

dcterms:description: Historical records of the number of books borrowed by students, used to predict library usage and academic performance.
dcterms:title: Historical number of borrowed books sequence

dcterms:description: Historical records of the number of failed courses for students, used to predict academic performance.
dcterms:title: Historical number of failed courses sequence
